In this 2-hour lab, students with prior experience in Python or R will work with Professor Jeff Levy to learn what makes a good code sample, and the merits and usage of the MATLAB language. We will then go over some similarities and differences between MATLAB and R/Python, and conclude with group work developing our own simple data analysis program in MATLAB.
Students will end this time with an understanding of how to leverage their Python/R experience to work in the MATLAB syntax, and with a working code sample suitable to include in job applications.

